sentences.english: Fruit-of Wudang Mountain in prestigious Ming Dynasty Wudang Mountain is the rare plant.

sentences.english: There remained much support for small-scale district control.
sentences.chinese: 小範圍的地區控制依然享有很多支持。

sentences.english: Trademark registrants enjoy trademark rights and receive protection under law.
sentences.chinese: 商標註冊人享有商標權，受法律保護。

sentences.english: Read your software contracts, and make sure you understand your licensing rights.

sentences.english: Article 3 The Macao Special Administrative Region shall be vested with independent judicial power, including that of final adjudication.
sentences.chinese: 第三條澳門特別行政區享有獨立的司法權和終審權。

sentences.english: Their employees enjoy life tenure and cannot be terminated.

sentences.english: Huayan is a very famous artist with good reputation in the Chinese painting history.

sentences.english: Article 105 Women enjoy equal rights with men in civil law.
sentences.chinese: 第一百零五條婦女享有同男子平等的民事權利。

sentences.english: Aquarians are good workers and usually are paid well.

sentences.english: Prisoners are accorded the material treatment necessary in their daily lives.

sentences.english: The joint co-owners shall undertake the rights and obligations with respect to the property under co-ownership.
sentences.chinese: 共同共有人對共有財產享有權利，承擔義務。

sentences.english: In addition, Jolie was estranged from her famous father.
sentences.chinese: 此外，朱莉與她享有盛譽的父親出現不和。

sentences.english: People who have close friends naturally enjoy their company.
sentences.chinese: 有至交者，自然享有友情之樂。

sentences.english: The high-quality service of this hotel has won a high reputation Both at home and aBroad.

sentences.english: It is greatly welcomed with a mass of enterprises and has built up a good company credit standing within and outside food industry.

sentences.english: Besides, the Taohuawu wood engraving Spring Festival pictures also enjoy great reputation.
sentences.chinese: 此外，桃花塢的木刻年畫也享有盛名。
